<HEADLINE>
<P>
OUTTAKES: QUIBBLES &amp; BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
. . . Nelson Entertainment's "The Taking of Beverly Hills" wrapped earlier this 
month on locations outside Mexico City -- but not before bandidos held up an 
armored van on the way to the set, getting away with $50,000 worth of pesos 
intended for crew members being paid in cash. 
</P>
<P>
. . . Get out your handkerchiefs: In the just-out "Ghost," Demi Moore has at 
least seven major crying jags following the death of her true love, Patrick 
Swayze. Meanwhile, hunk Swayze puts in three shirtless scenes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
