<HEADLINE>
<P>
MIXED MEDIA; 
</P>
<P>
*** "LIVE ON BROADWAY" BARRY MANILOW 6 WEST VIDEOCASSETTE ($19.98): ITEMS IN 
THIS SURVEY OF POP-RELATED VIDEOS, BOOKS AND LASER DISCS ARE RATED ON A SCALE 
OF ONE STAR (POOR) TO FIVE (A CLASSIC). 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS HUNT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Manilow appeals mainly to the straight-laced, over-35 crowd that prefers 
ballads brimming with melodrama -- the chief ingredient in Manilow staples like 
"Mandy" and "I Write the Songs." 
</P>
<P>
That audience should love this swiftly-paced, well-produced, 90-minute tape of 
Manilow's Broadway show -- with the songs structured around key points in his 
life and career. Though mainly a solo show, Manilow uses supporting performers 
for several numbers. Never an exceptional singer, he makes maximum use of his 
strengths -- earnestness, an amiable personality and a knack for making his 
audience feel warm and comfortable. DENNIS HUNT 
</P>
