<TEXT>
<P>
This is one woman's view of trying to get by in an all-too-loveless world, and 
in the choice selection of material from a variety of writers, this Kentucky 
wonder exudes a steely resolve that never gives in to self-pity. Instead, she 
relies on a great sense of humor and an unflagging faith that things will get 
better, even when disappointment strikes. As a singer, she may not plumb the 
depths of the human soul as Emmylou Harris can, but she compensates with miles 
and miles of heart. RANDY LEWIS 
