<P>
FOR SOME READERS, TIFFANY IS NO JETSON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An item in the July 8 Outtakes column begins, "One person who won't be buying a 
ticket to 'Jetsons: The Movie': actress Janet Waldo." Make it three: Janet 
Waldo, my sister and I. 
</P>
<P>
I was pretty excited when I heard that the Jetsons were coming out in an 
animated feature. 
</P>
<P>
I grew up with that cartoon. Then I read many articles concerning this Judy 
Jetson incident, one being Kyle Counts' Outtakes item, "Not a Genuine Tiffany." 
</P>
<P>
From just listening to Judy Jetson's voice in the movie previews, I could not 
connect with the Jetsons. It just wasn't the same Jetsons I grew up with. Judy 
Jetson was not the real Judy Jetson without Janet Waldo's voice. The Judy I 
heard was an imposter. 
</P>
<P>
I'm sure many people feel the same way. How could Hanna-Barbera (the producers) 
do such a thing?! It boils down to greed. Why couldn't Tiffany just be happy 
with recording the soundtrack? Did she have to steal Waldo's role as well? 
</P>
<P>
CHRISTINA Y. CHANG 
</P>
<P>
Palos Verdes 
</P>
<P>
 Waldo, the voice of Judy Jetson in the animated TV series, had reprised the 
role in the movie before being replaced by singer Tiffany. 
</P>
