<HEADLINE>
<P>
AWAY FROM IT ALL ON THE BIG ISLAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JERRY HULSE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sightseeing: Scenery on the Big Island from lush tropical growth to desert-like 
terrain. Recommended visits: the bay south of Kailua-Kona, where Capt. James 
Cook met his Waterloo and the orchid farms at Hilo. 
</P>
<P>
Kona Arts Center, P.O. Box 272, Holualoa, Kona, Hawaii 96725, (808) 322-2307. 
</P>
<P>
Tours of the Waipio Valley are available through Waipio Valley Shuttle &amp; 
Tours, P.O. Box 5128, Kukuihaele, Hawaii 96727, (808) 775-7121. 
</P>
<P>
For information on volcanoes, contact Volcanoes National Park, Box 52, Hawaii 
National Park, Hawaii 96718, (808) 967-7311. 
</P>
<P>
For additional details, contact the Hawaii Visitors Bureau, 180 Kinoole St., 
Hilo, Hawaii 96720, (808) 961-5797. In California, contact the HVB, 3440 
Wilshire Blvd., Suite 502, Los Angeles 90010, (213) 385-5301. 
</P>
<P>
Little Hotels and B&amp;Bs: Holualoa Inn, P.O. Box 222, Holualoa, Hawaii 96725, 
(808) 324-1121. Possibly the finest B&amp;B in Hawaii. Four rooms, a swimming 
pool, fireplace, billiards room. Rates: $60/$125 with a 15% discount for guests 
remaining a week. 
</P>
<P>
Kona Hotel, P.O. Box 342, Holualoa, Hawaii 96725, (808) 324-1155. Eleven rooms, 
shared baths. A bit ramshackle but plenty of old Hawaii atmosphere. Rates: $15 
single, $23 double. 
</P>
<P>
Manago Hotel, P.O. Box 145, Captain Cook, Hawaii 96704, (808) 323-2642. 
Forty-two rooms, an informal restaurant with tasty, inexpensive fare. Rates: 
$18/$32 single, $21/$35 double. Japanese style: $46 single, $49 double. 
</P>
<P>
Jacqueline Horne's Waipio Wayside Inn, P.O. 840, Honokaa, Hawaii 96727, (808) 
775-0275. Four rooms (one with private bath). Rates: $45/$65. Call (800) 
833-8849. 
</P>
<P>
Waipio Hotel, Waipio Valley, Hawaii. Contact Tom Araki, 25 Malama Place, Hilo, 
Hawaii 96720 (no telephone). Five rooms. Rates: $15 per night. 
</P>
<P>
Linda Beech's Tree House, P.O. Box 5086, Honokaa, Hawaii 96727, (808) 775-9518. 
Rates: $125. JERRY HULSE 
</P>
