feet from the Oceanside pier. ; Photo, "Old" but very fit lifeguards Tom 
Buckner, left, and Matt Stephens. ; Photo, As part of their killer workout, 
Oceanside lifeguards must be able to run 1 mile, slosh quickly around the 
1,900-foot pier, above, then run another mile, all in less than 27 minutes. ; 
Photo, The regimen is designed to keep them strong and fast enough to plow 
through waves in emergency rescues. ; Photo, (A2) Different Strokes: Lifeguards 
Matt Stephens and Tom Buckner have lost count of the people they have pulled 
from the crashing surf off Oceanside. To keep in shape, lifeguard captain 
Stephens devised a regimen that requires his 33-member crew to run a mile, jump 
40 feet from the Oceanside pier, swim around it, then run another mile -- all 
within 27 minutes. BRUCE K. HUFF / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
