<P>
Photo, COLOR, Doctor-playwright David Feldshuh, top, says "Miss Evers' Boys" is 
"not a vendetta." Rosemary Kaul / Los Angeles Times; Photo, COLOR, Charles 
Lanyer, rear left, Starletta DuPois give treatment to Carl Lumbly. RANDY 
LEFFINGWELL / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
<TYPE>
<P>
Profile; Main Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
FELDSHUH, DAVID; MISS EVERS' BOYS (PLAY); BLACKS -- HEALTH; MEDICAL RESEARCH; 
VENEREAL DISEASES; MEDICAL ETHICS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA071590-0112 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 247493 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
July 15, 1990, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
