<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRITICS' CHOICE: COMING OUT UNDER FIRE THE HISTORY OF GAY MEN AND WOMEN IN 
WORLD WAR TWO BY ALLAN BERUBE(THE FREE PRESS: $22.95; 377 PP.) 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
" . . . a rich social history that argues that much of contemporary homosexual 
identity, sense of community, and activism had its origin in the experience of 
gay men and women in World War II . . . a passionate book without ever becoming 
a polemical one." -- Neil Miller 
