<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENTS: A GUIDE TO THE BEST OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA; 
</P>
<P>
SHOPTALK; 
</P>
<P>
BOOKS TO TRAVEL BY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBIN TUCKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
THESE DAYS, Adrian Kalvinskas isn't traveling much, but he's learning a lot 
about the world. As owner of Distant Lands -- A Traveler's Bookstore, 
Kalvinskas gets a lot of off-the-wall questions about a lot of off-the-wall 
places. 
</P>
<P>
"It's a real education," he says. 
</P>
<P>
The small, comfortable shop invites intense browsing. In addition to maps, 
4,500 travel titles and a wide selection of travel videos, Kalvinskas stocks an 
extensive armchair-travel section. "It's less dry to take an armchair adventure 
than to read a guidebook," he believes. "Travel literature gives a better idea 
of people and place." 
</P>
<P>
Kalvinskas grew up in the Pasadena area and, after following his own 
wanderlust, decided to become involved in the evolution of Old Pasadena. "It's 
a lot of fun," he says of running such a bookstore. "Ninety-nine percent of the 
time people come in happy because they're excited about traveling." 
</P>
<P>
Distant Lands -- A Traveler's Bookstore, 62 S. Raymond Ave., Old Pasadena; 
(818) 449-3220. ROBIN TUCKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
