<P>
BABY CAKES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DEBORAH SROLOFF 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOMETIMES THE grandest gesture is best served by the smallest of trinkets. 
</P>
<P>
And while the miniature wedding cakes sold at The Bakery on Melrose aren't 
exactly Cartier, they are jewels in their own right. Just 5 inches in diameter 
and 6 inches high, these three-tiered cakes are perfect, tiny versions of the 
traditional wedding cake. 
</P>
<P>
The mini-cakes ($22.50 each) come in white- or chocolate-cake versions with 
apricot or raspberry filling, and The Bakery prides itself on using only pure, 
natural ingredients and flavorings. What could be more perfect for an 
anniversary celebration -- or perhaps to sweeten a marriage proposal? 
</P>
<P>
The Bakery on Melrose, 7261 Melrose Ave., Los Angeles; (213) 934-4493.DEBORAH 
SROLOFF 
</P>
