<TEXT>
<P>
A flash fire eight levels below the flight deck of the aircraft carrier 
Saratoga injured three civilian welders and a sailor, the Navy said. 
</P>
<P>
None of the injuries were life-threatening. Damage to the ship docked at 
Mayport Naval Station, Fla., was minimal and the fire burned itself out almost 
immediately, officials said. The Saratoga is based at Mayport and carries a 
crew of about 5,000 when fully staffed. It has been undergoing minor repairs 
since returning in June from training operations along the Eastern seaboard. 
