<HEADLINE>
<P>
'VOTERS GIVE CONGRESSMEN GOOD REVIEWS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The impression one gets from the results of the Times Orange County Poll on 
voters' attitudes toward Orange County congressmen ("O.C. Voters Give 
Congressmen Good Reviews," July 9) is not that these lawmakers are popular, but 
that their performance is predominantly uninspiring. 
</P>
<P>
While it is true, for example, that Dannemeyer received the highest favorable 
rating (33% of those polled), 67% of voters either had no opinion of him or 
found him unfavorable. Opinions regarding the other congressmen showed even 
greater indifference. What this all seems to say is that what is truly 
conservative about Orange County is not necessarily its politics, but its 
enthusiasm for its politicians. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN McGOWAN 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton 
</P>
</TEXT>
