<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE NEWS: ASSOCIATE PROFESSOR AT CALTECH GETS FELLOWSHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yaser S. Abu-Mostafa, associate professor of electrical engineering and 
computer science at Caltech, has been awarded the Richard P. Feynman-Hughes 
Fellowship. 
</P>
<P>
The fellowship is awarded annually to a young member of the faculty in the 
division of engineering and applied science. It provides research support of 
$30,000 each year and may be renewed annually for up to three years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
