<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN CROSSING STREET KILLED BY CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 72-year-old woman was struck and killed by a motorist Saturday night as she 
was trying to walk across a busy street, Santa Ana police said. 
</P>
<P>
Thelma L. Wolfe of Santa Ana was killed as she was trying to cross West 1st 
Street midway between Broadway and Ross Street about 6:10 p.m., Police Sgt. 
Rich Murg said. 
</P>
<P>
"She walked right in front of the car," Murg said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver of the 1979 Mercury Zephyr that struck Wolfe was not cited, Murg 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
TRAFFIC ACCIDENTS -- ORANGE COUNTY; PEDESTRIANS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA071590-0212 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 247783 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
July 15, 1990, Sunday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
